  <h2>The Galigopuram</h2>
  <div style="display:flex; gap:26px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 200 470" style="width:118px; color:var(--ink); flex:0 0 auto"
         role="img" aria-label="The 135-foot Galigopuram: seven tiers above a gateway, a flared shikhara, five kalasas along the ridge">
      <use href="#gopuram" />
    </svg>
    <div style="flex:1 1 16rem">
      <p>
        The tower stands <strong>135 feet</strong> and was not raised at once. The first
        storey belongs to the Vijayanagara period and the reign of Krishnadeva Raya; the
        walls went up around 1425; the upper storeys were added in <strong>1837</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Seven tiers recede above a tall plain gateway, each face carrying rows of niches,
        and the barrel-vaulted shikhara at the summit flares wider than the tier beneath
        it, carrying five kalasas along its ridge.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

